
[1]niceness

   NICENESS, n.

   1. Delicacy of perception; the quality of perceiving small differences;
   as niceness of taste.

   2. Extreme delicacy; excess of scrupulousness or exactness.

   Unlike the niceness of our modern dames.

   3. Accuracy; minute exactness; as niceness of work; niceness of texture
   or proportion.

   Wheres now the labored niceness in thy dress?
